    "title": "油泼面宫格漫画图",
    "title_en": "Oil-Splashed Noodles Grid Comic",
    "prompt": "编写一个 Nano Banana 提示词，用于生成「油泼面的做法」四宫格漫画图，有配图和文字排版。",
    "prompt_en": "Write a Nano Banana prompt for generating a four-panel comic strip of \"How to Make Oil-Splashed Noodles\" with illustrations and text layout.",
    "source": "https://x.com/hellokaton/status/1991668144080056423",
    "type": "t2i",
    "author": "@hellokaton",
    "author_link": "https://x.com/hellokaton/status/1991668144080056423",
    "revised_prompt": "一张宽幅的手绘美食漫画图，整体采用温馨的日式水彩手绘风格，背景为带有细微纸张纹理的浅米色。画面采用左侧图文介绍、右侧四宫格步骤的横向排版构图。\n\n画面左侧上方用醒目的黑色毛笔质感大字体写着主标题 '油泼面的做法'。标题下方是一行稍小的红色副标题 '准备食材：宽面、葱花、蒜末、辣椒面、生抽、陈醋、食用油'。在文字下方，错落有致地画着几组细腻的手绘食材小插图：一束扎着红绳的生宽面条、两瓣带皮的大蒜、一根鲜红的小辣椒、一个小瓷罐装着的辣椒面以及一把木勺。\n\n画面的右侧区域占据了整体三分之二的宽度，是一个由棕色细线勾勒出的 2x2 四宫格漫画，按图文顺序展示具体的制作步骤：\n\n左上方的第一个格子展示步骤一。画面中心是一个带有蓝色花纹的青花瓷大圆碗，碗内盛着冒着淡淡热气的煮熟白色宽面条。面条正中央高高堆起一小撮切碎的绿色葱花、白色蒜末和鲜红色的辣椒面。格子底部的黄色横向矩形文本框内写着黑色文字：'第一步：宽面煮熟捞出装碗，铺上葱花、蒜末、辣椒面。'\n\n右上方的第二个格子展示步骤二。画面视角拉近，一把带长柄的银色小铁勺正倾倒出滚烫发亮的透明热油。热油精准地浇在碗中心的辣椒面和蒜末上，接触的瞬间迸发出向四周飞溅的细小金黄色油花和升腾的白色蒸汽。热气特效旁带有醒目的红色动态漫画拟声词 '滋啦——'。格子底部的黄色文本框内写着黑色文字：'第二步：烧热一勺食用油，迅速泼在食材上，激发出浓郁香气。'\n\n左下方的第三个格子展示步骤三。一只手拿着小木勺，正往刚才泼好油的面碗中倒入深棕色的调料液体。面碗旁边放置着两个带有日式复古标签的玻璃调料瓶，标签上分别写着 '生抽' 和 '陈醋'。格子底部的黄色文本框内写着黑色文字：'第三步：根据个人口味加入适量生抽、陈醋、少许盐提鲜。'\n\n右下方的第四个格子展示最终成品。一双竹筷子正从碗中挑起一大坨搅拌均匀的宽面，面条表面裹满了红亮诱人的红油酱汁，质感油润透亮。碗的周围画着代表香气的淡黄色波浪线和小星星闪烁特效，极具视觉食欲感。格子底部的黄色文本框内写着黑色文字：'第四步：趁热将面条与调料搅拌均匀，一碗香气扑鼻的油泼面就完成啦！'\n\n整体画面色调温暖、高饱和，重点突出红油的透亮和面条的诱人质感。光线明亮，文字排版对齐工整，字迹清晰可辨，兼具菜谱的实用说明功能与漫画的生动趣味性。",
    "image": "https://eb118-file.cdn.bcebos.com/ernie-image/gallery_41_4.png",
    "revised_prompt_en": "A wide-format hand-drawn food comic illustration, rendered entirely in a warm Japanese-style watercolor hand-drawn aesthetic, with a light beige background featuring subtle paper texture. The composition adopts a horizontal layout with text and illustration introductions on the left and a four-panel step-by-step grid on the right.\n\nIn the upper-left of the image, a prominent main title is written in bold black brush-textured large font reading 'How to Make Oil-Splashed Noodles (油泼面)'. Below the title is a slightly smaller red subtitle reading 'Ingredients: wide noodles, chopped scallions, minced garlic, chili flake powder, light soy sauce, aged black vinegar, cooking oil'. Beneath the text, several delicate hand-drawn ingredient illustrations are arranged in a staggered layout: a bundle of raw wide noodles tied with a red string, two cloves of garlic with skin, a bright red small chili pepper, a small ceramic jar filled with chili flake powder, and a wooden spoon.\n\nThe right-side area of the image occupies roughly two-thirds of the total width and features a 2×2 four-panel comic grid outlined with fine brown lines, presenting the preparation steps in sequential order:\n\nThe upper-left panel illustrates Step One. At the center of the panel is a large blue-and-white porcelain bowl with traditional blue floral patterns, filled with cooked white wide noodles emitting faint wisps of steam. On top of the noodles, a small mound of chopped green scallions, white minced garlic, and vibrant red chili flake powder is piled high in the center. At the bottom of the panel, a yellow horizontal rectangular text box contains black text reading: 'Step 1: Boil the wide noodles until cooked, drain, and place in a bowl. Top with scallions, minced garlic, and chili flake powder.'\n\nThe upper-right panel illustrates Step Two. The viewing angle is closer. A small silver long-handled iron ladle is tilting and pouring out sizzling, glistening transparent hot oil. The hot oil is precisely poured onto the chili flake powder and minced garlic at the center of the bowl. At the moment of contact, tiny golden oil droplets splatter outward in all directions accompanied by rising white steam. Next to the steam effect is a prominent red dynamic comic onomatopoeia reading '滋啦——' (Sizzle——). At the bottom of the panel, a yellow text box contains black text reading: 'Step 2: Heat a ladle of cooking oil until smoking hot, then quickly splash it over the toppings to release an intense aroma.'\n\nThe lower-left panel illustrates Step Three. A hand holding a small wooden spoon is pouring dark brown seasoning liquid into the oil-splashed noodle bowl. Beside the bowl are two glass condiment bottles with Japanese retro-style labels, reading '生抽' (light soy sauce) and '陈醋' (aged black vinegar) respectively. At the bottom of the panel, a yellow text box contains black text reading: 'Step 3: Add light soy sauce, aged black vinegar, and a pinch of salt to taste for enhanced flavor.'\n\nThe lower-right panel showcases the final finished dish. A pair of bamboo chopsticks is lifting a generous tangle of well-tossed wide noodles from the bowl. The noodle surface is fully coated in a glossy, appetizing red chili oil sauce, with an oily, lustrous, and translucent sheen.",
