    "revised_prompt": "这是一张面向小学三年级学生的横版信息图海报，整体视觉风格模仿艾瑞·卡尔（Eric Carle）的标志性手绘彩色薄纸拼贴画（tissue paper collage）艺术风格。画面充满了鲜艳的色彩叠加、明显的画笔涂刷纹理以及仿佛用剪刀剪裁出的不规则纸片边缘，充满童趣和手工感。画面背景为带有微小颗粒质感的米白色纸纹。\n\n海报正上方中央有醒目的拼贴感英文字母，主标题为大号的粗体字 'THE FOUR SEASONS IN TORONTO'，正下方跟随一行稍小的副标题 'CANADA'。\n\n画面主体横向并排划分为四个垂直的矩形版块，每个版块分别展示多伦多的一个季节，版块之间有细微的留白分割。\n\n最左侧为春季版块：最上方用带有绿色水彩笔触纹理的拼贴字母写着 'SPRING'。插图包含天空中几滴蓝紫色渐变的硕大雨滴，下方地面上是几朵绽放的粉红色和深红色郁金香，以及带有刷痕的嫩绿色草叶拼贴。画面最下方有两行清晰的黑色手写体英文：'Rain melts the snow. Tulips bloom at High Park!'\n\n左起第二个为夏季版块：最上方用带有亮黄色和橙色混合纹理的字母写着 'SUMMER'。插图的中心是一个巨大的、带有放射状橙黄色浓烈笔触的太阳，下方是带有深蓝色水波纹理的安大略湖水。背景中有一座用红色和白色纸条拼贴出的极简CN塔（加拿大国家电视塔）剪影。画面最下方写着英文：'The sun is hot! We play at the beach by Lake Ontario.'\n\n左起第三个为秋季版块：最上方用带有橙红色和棕色纹理的字母写着 'AUTUMN'。插图描绘了一棵树，树干呈现棕色木纹质感，树冠由大块的红色、橙色、黄色碎纸片拼贴交叠而成，几片具有加拿大特色的红色枫叶正随着几条淡蓝色的风线在空中飘落。画面最下方写着英文：'Leaves turn red and orange. Time to wear a light jacket.'\n\n最右侧为冬季版块：最上方用带有冰蓝色纹理的字母写着 'WINTER'。插图背景变成了偏冷的淡蓝色，天空中散布着许多用白色打孔纸片代表的雪花。地面是起伏的白色雪堆拼贴。画面中央是一个穿着厚重冬装的拼贴小人，戴着红色的毛线帽，穿着厚蓝色外套和绿色围巾，脚穿冰鞋在冰面上滑行。画面最下方写着英文：'It snows a lot! We go ice skating at Nathan Phillips Square.'\n\n所有文字内容均完整、清晰可见，整张海报的构图紧凑，每一个视觉元素都展现出经典绘本中那种色彩斑驳且极具层次感的手工拼贴艺术特征。",
    "image": "https://eb118-file.cdn.bcebos.com/ernie-image/gallery_43_3.png",
    "revised_prompt_en": "This is a landscape-format infographic poster designed for third-grade elementary students. Its overall visual style imitates Eric Carle's iconic hand-painted tissue paper collage art style. The image is filled with vivid color overlays, prominent brushstroke textures, and irregular paper-edge cutouts as if trimmed with scissors, brimming with childlike charm and a handmade feel. The background has an off-white paper texture with a subtle grainy quality.\n\nCentered at the very top of the poster are eye-catching collage-style English letters. The main title in large bold type reads 'THE FOUR SEASONS IN TORONTO,' with a slightly smaller subtitle 'CANADA' directly beneath it.\n\nThe main body of the image is divided horizontally into four side-by-side vertical rectangular panels, each showcasing one season in Toronto, separated by subtle white-space gaps.\n\nThe leftmost panel is the spring section: at the very top, collage letters with green watercolor brushstroke texture spell 'SPRING.' The illustrations include several large blue-to-purple gradient raindrops in the sky, a few blooming pink and deep red tulips on the ground below, and tender green grass blade collages with visible brush marks. At the very bottom of the panel are two lines of clear black handwritten English: 'Rain melts the snow. Tulips bloom at High Park!'\n\nThe second panel from the left is the summer section: at the top, letters with bright yellow and orange mixed textures spell 'SUMMER.' The central illustration features a huge sun with radial orange-yellow intense brushstrokes, below which is Lake Ontario water rendered with deep blue wave textures. In the background is a minimalist CN Tower (Canada's National Tower) silhouette collaged from red and white paper strips. At the bottom it reads: 'The sun is hot! We play at the beach by Lake Ontario.'\n\nThe third panel from the left is the autumn section: at the top, letters with orange-red and brown textures spell 'AUTUMN.' The illustration depicts a tree with a brown wood-grain textured trunk, its canopy composed of large overlapping torn pieces of red, orange, and yellow paper collage. Several distinctively Canadian red maple leaves drift through the air along a few pale blue wind lines. At the bottom it reads: 'Leaves turn red an",
