    "revised_prompt_en": "An inner-page layout illustration for a product design catalogue, with an overall horizontal wide-format proportion and a base tone exhibiting a warm, neutral paper texture. The layout presents a clean architectural sensibility, primarily divided into a lifestyle product hero image in the upper area and a technical specifications panel in the lower area.\n\nThe upper half of the composition occupies the majority of the visual space, showcasing a modern lounge chair in a minimalist, highly realistic editorial-grade photography style. The chair body consists of a curved walnut backrest panel, a silver brushed stainless-steel support frame, and a beige linen seat cushion, placed centered and slightly above middle. Its setting is a minimalist architectural interior scene, with a warm-toned plaster wall featuring delicate texture behind it, and a light-grey concrete floor surface with subtle natural mottling. A beam of angled natural sunlight illuminates the chair from the side, casting soft yet sharply contrasting diagonal shadows on the wall and floor. Generous breathing whitespace surrounds the product, and the overall photographic tone is warm, soft, and richly textured.\n\nThe lower half of the composition is a technical specifications panel arranged in a modular grid. In the lower-left and lower-center areas of the panel, three orthographic projection architectural drawings of the chair are displayed, rendered with slender dark-brown technical lines. The leftmost is the front elevation of the chair, accompanied by fine dimension annotation lines and text reading 'H 780 mm' and 'W 650 mm'; the middle is the side elevation, with dimension annotations 'SH 420 mm' and 'D 700 mm'; to the right of the drawing area is a three-quarter angle internal sectional view, from which two thin leader lines extend, connecting to minimal structural description texts reading 'Ergonomic plywood shell' and 'High-density foam'.\n\nThe lower-right area of the bottom half features three square physical material sample swatches arranged in a row. From left to right, the first sample displays a beige linen fabric texture, with minimal dark-brown small text at the bottom reading 'Premium Linen Blend / Beige'; the second sample displays walnut wood grain, annotated below as 'Bent Walnut Veneer / Matte Finish'; the third sample displays a brushed stainless-steel metal texture, annotated below as 'Brushed Stainless Steel / Grade 304'.\n\nAll text annotations throughout the entire illustration use soft dark-brown or black, with small font sizes and restrained typesetting, without any exaggerated large",
