    "revised_prompt_en": "A landscape-oriented (approximately 4:3 ratio), whimsical children's crayon hand-drawn style illustration, presented as a warm and joyful city travel diary. The background has a soft, pale yellow drawing-paper texture, employing vivid and bright colors such as bright red, sky blue, and grass green, with strokes exhibiting the distinctly rough, textured quality of crayon doodling. Centered at the very top of the image, a large title 'Tokyo Travel Journal' is written in colorful handwritten lettering. The visual center of the image is a winding, zigzagging travel route composed of colorful dashed lines and arrows, traversing the entire image from left to right. The route comprises four stops of a one-day Tokyo tour: at the starting point on the left, handwritten text reads 'Stop 1: Senso-ji Temple - Giant red lantern!', accompanied by a drawing of a red Kaminarimon giant lantern; the dashed line meanders to the lower right toward the left-center, where it reads 'Stop 2: Akihabara - Anime wonderland!', paired with a chibi-style retro game console doodle; the dashed line continues curving to the upper right, reading 'Stop 3: Shibuya Crossing - So many people!', accompanied by black-and-white zebra crossing stripes and a few stick-figure drawings; finally, the dashed line leads to the endpoint on the right side, reading 'Final Stop: Ramen & Takoyaki - Best dinner ever!', with a steaming bowl of ramen drawn beside it. Scattered densely around the route are chibi-style cute hand-drawn elements: in the lower-left corner, a little boy explorer wearing a yellow backpack and holding up binoculars has a speech bubble above his head with the childlike exclamation 'I didn't know Tokyo was so fun!'; in the lower-right corner, a cute little girl biting into a pink strawberry daifuku has a speech bubble reading 'I want to come again!'. The upper half of the image features scattered chibi city landmarks: the upper left has a towering 'Tokyo Skytree' doodle, the upper right has a red-and-white striped 'Tokyo Tower', and in the far background at the top center is a snow-capped 'Mt. Fuji'. Several whimsical signposts are planted along the route: near Kaminarimon, a bright yellow sign reads 'Crowds ahead!'; near the Shibuya zebra crossing...",
    "prompt_zh": "请创建一张色彩鲜艳的、儿童蜡笔画风格的竖版（9:16）插画，标题为\"{City Name}旅行手账\"。\n这幅作品应看起来像是一个充满好奇心的孩子用彩色蜡笔画的，采用柔和、温暖的浅色调背景（如淡黄色），搭配明亮的红色、蓝色、绿色和其他欢快的颜色，营造出温馨、童趣的旅行氛围。\n\n一、主场景：旅行手账风格的路线图\n\n在插画中央，绘制一条\"蜿蜒曲折的旅行路线\"，用箭头和虚线连接多个地点。\n路线应自动"
