    "revised_prompt_en": "A 16:9 landscape-oriented children's crayon-style hand-drawn travel diary illustration. The background is a soft, warm light yellow, accented with bright red, blue, and green, exuding a cheerful, cozy, and playful atmosphere. All text is in cute, childlike handwritten English lettering, with strokes simulating the rough texture of real crayons.\n\nIn the upper-left corner, a prominent large title reads 'Beijing Travel Journal'. Spanning across the center of the image is a winding, zigzagging travel route composed of colorful dashed lines and hand-drawn arrows. Four main stops are distributed along the route, each accompanied by text descriptions and corresponding chibi-style small illustrations:\nAt the starting point of the route, it reads 'Stop 1: The Forbidden City - So many red walls!', with a simple sketch of a palace featuring red walls and yellow-tiled roofs drawn beside it.\nFollowing the arrow to the right, the second stop reads 'Stop 2: Temple of Heaven - A big round roof!', paired with a doodle-style illustration of the Hall of Prayer for Good Harvests with its round-domed architecture.\nContinuing along, the third stop reads 'Stop 3: The Great Wall - I climbed really high!', with a gray, winding section of wall and a small watchtower drawn beside it.\nThe endpoint of the route is in the lower-right corner, reading 'Final Stop: Peking Duck - Super crispy and yummy!', accompanied by a steaming, plump little roast duck icon.\n\nScattered in a staggered arrangement around the route are many adorably naïve doodle characters and decorative elements. In the lower-left area, a happy child wearing a yellow short-sleeved shirt is holding up a string of bright red tanghulu (candied hawthorn). In the upper-right area, a little explorer wearing a blue backpack and an explorer hat is drawn. Along the roadside, several crooked wooden signposts are planted, with directional messages reading: 'Don't get lost!', 'Crowds ahead!', and 'Yummy food this way!'.\n\nBlank spaces throughout the image are dotted with colorful sticker-style phrases: 'Beijing travel memories unlocked!', 'Beijing food adventu...'",
