    "revised_prompt": "一张竖版的信息图海报，详细展示了传统青瓷的制作过程。海报背景为仿古的米黄色羊皮纸纹理，四周边缘带有淡淡的棕色晕染效果，整体呈现淡雅的中国风水彩插画风格。画面顶部居中位置印有黑色的大字标题，写着 '青瓷制作技艺'，下方配有较小的深灰色英文字幕 'HOW IT IS MADE: TRADITIONAL CELADON'。海报主体自上而下分为四个图文并茂的区块，每个区块左侧是水彩插画，右侧是文字说明。\n\n第一个区块左侧画着一双沾满泥污的手，正在一张粗糙的木桌上用力揉按一团灰色的陶土。右侧顶部用加粗字体写着 '第一步：揉泥'，下方是一段说明文字，内容为 '将高岭土加水调和，反复揉搓，挤出泥团中的空气，使泥料变得致密均匀，防止烧制时开裂。'\n\n第二个区块左侧画着一个正在旋转的陶轮，一双灵巧的手正将泥团向上提拉，塑造成一个细颈花瓶的雏形，花瓶周围带有表现旋转的动感线条。右侧写着 '第二步：拉坯'，说明文字为 '将揉好的泥团放置在辘轳上，随着转盘快速旋转，工匠利用双手的光滑与力量，将泥团拉伸、塑造成所需的器型。'\n\n第三个区块左侧画着一只手捏着干燥的花瓶底部，将其一半倾斜浸入一个装满淡青色釉浆的大木桶中，几滴釉浆正顺着瓶身滴落，桶边溅起微小的水花。右侧文字为 '第三步：施釉'，说明文字为 '待素胎自然阴干后，在其表面均匀涂抹或浸入特制的青釉浆中。釉料的厚度和配方决定了最终成品的温润光泽。'\n\n第四个区块左侧画着一座传统的砖砌柴窑，半圆形的窑门敞开，里面透出明亮的橙红色火焰，火光照亮了周围的红砖，隐约可见窑内摆放的匣钵。右侧文字为 '第四步：烧窑'，说明文字为 '将施釉后的素胎装入匣钵，送入窑炉。在高达1300摄氏度的高温下还原烧制，泥土与釉料发生化学反应，最终浴火重生。'\n\n画面最底部居中有一行小字 '传承千年匠心，感受泥土与火焰的艺术'，文字右侧印有一个小巧的方形红色印章，印章内写着繁体字 '匠心'。整体排版对齐工整，色彩以泥灰色、淡青色和木棕色为主，光线柔和，清晰度高，兼具科普说明功能与艺术美感。",
    "image": "https://eb118-file.cdn.bcebos.com/ernie-image/gallery_76_2.png",
    "revised_prompt_en": "A vertical-format infographic poster detailing the production process of traditional celadon. The poster background features an antique cream-colored parchment texture, with faint brown vignette effects around the edges, presenting an overall understated Chinese-style watercolor illustration aesthetic. At the top center, a large black title reads '青瓷制作技艺' (Celadon Craftsmanship), with a smaller dark gray English subtitle beneath it: 'HOW IT IS MADE: TRADITIONAL CELADON'. The main body of the poster is divided from top to bottom into four illustrated sections, each with a watercolor illustration on the left and text descriptions on the right.\n\nThe first section shows on the left a pair of mud-covered hands vigorously kneading a lump of gray clay on a rough wooden table. On the right, the heading in bold reads '第一步：揉泥' (Step One: Kneading the Clay), with an explanatory paragraph below: 'Mix kaolin clay with water, knead repeatedly to expel air from the clay mass, making the material dense and uniform to prevent cracking during firing.'\n\nThe second section shows on the left a spinning potter's wheel, with a pair of dexterous hands pulling the clay upward, shaping the nascent form of a slender-necked vase, with dynamic motion lines around the vase suggesting rotation. On the right, it reads '第二步：拉坯' (Step Two: Throwing on the Wheel), with the description: 'Place the kneaded clay on the potter's wheel (lulu); as the turntable spins rapidly, the craftsman uses the smoothness and strength of both hands to stretch and shape the clay into the desired vessel form.'\n\nThe third section shows on the left a hand gripping the base of a dried vase, tilting it halfway into a large wooden barrel filled with pale celadon-colored glaze slurry, with a few drops of glaze dripping down the body and tiny splashes at the barrel's edge. The text on the right reads '第三步：施釉' (Step Three: Glazing), with the description: 'After the bisque body has naturally air-dried, evenly coat or dip it into specially formulated celadon glaze slurry. The thickness and formula of the glaze determine the warm luster of the final product.'\n\nThe fourth section shows on the left a traditional brick-built wood-fired kiln, with a semicircular kiln door open, revealing bright orange-red flames inside; the firelight illuminates the surrounding red bricks, and saggars (firing containers) are faintly visible inside the kiln. The text on the right reads '第四步：烧窑' (Step Four: Kiln Firing), with the description: 'Load the glazed bisque bodies into saggars and place them into the kiln. Under reduction firing at temperatures reaching 1300 degrees Celsius, the clay and glaze undergo chemical reactions, ultimately reborn through fire.'\n\nAt the very bottom center of the image, a line of small text reads '传承千年匠心，感受泥土与火焰的艺术' (Inheriting a millennium of craftsmanship, experiencing the art of earth and fire), with a small square red seal stamp to the right of the text, inside which is written in traditional...",
