    "revised_prompt": "一张手机社交APP的竖屏图文教程截图，采用从上到下的瀑布流排版。整体背景为温馨的浅米色，呈现出日系清新的美食排版风格。画面最顶部有手机系统的状态栏，清晰显示时间 '14:30'、5G信号图标、Wi-Fi图标和满格电池图标。\n\n状态栏下方，是居中排版的大字号主标题，深棕色粗体文字 '法式草莓慕斯蛋糕 零失败教程'，标题下方有一行较小的浅粉色英文副标题 'Strawberry Mousse Cake Recipe'。\n\n标题下方占据画面约三分之一比例的是一张高清的成品展示主图：放置在白色大理石圆盘上的一个6寸粉色慕斯蛋糕。蛋糕表面呈现光滑的镜面效果，顶部点缀着几颗切半的鲜亮红草莓和零星的高光金箔。背景是景深模糊的浅色原木桌面和一小枝尤加利叶，光线为柔和明亮的侧边自然光，突出了蛋糕绵密的质感和诱人的色泽。\n\n主图下方分为四个垂直排列的制作步骤区域。每个步骤区域左侧是一张带圆角的方形实拍过程图，右侧是对齐的黑色说明文字。\n\n第一步，左侧小图显示一双手正用金属勺背将深棕色的饼干碎压实在一个圆形脱底模具内。右侧文字排版整齐：'1. 饼干底：将80g消化饼干捣碎，加入40g融化的无盐黄油拌匀，铺入6寸模具底部压实，放入冰箱冷藏备用。'\n\n第二步，左侧小图是一个导热板上的银色小奶锅，里面正在熬煮翻滚的暗红色草莓果肉，上方带有淡淡的白色蒸汽。右侧文字为：'2. 草莓夹心：200g新鲜草莓切丁，加30g白砂糖和少许柠檬汁熬煮至浓稠，加入泡软的吉利丁片（5g），倒入小号模具冷冻定型。'\n\n第三步，左侧小图显示在一个大透明玻璃碗中，带有柔和浅粉色调的液体正被一把白色硅胶刮刀从下往上翻拌。右侧文字为：'3. 慕斯液：250g草莓打成泥，微微加热后融化10g吉利丁片。降温放凉后，与200g打发至6分发的淡奶油轻柔翻拌均匀。'\n\n第四步，左侧小图展示粉色的慕斯液正顺着碗口倾倒进模具中，模具中间隐约可见深红色的冻夹心层。右侧文字为：'4. 组合脱模：将一半慕斯液倒入模具，放入冷冻好的夹心，接着倒入剩余慕斯液填满抹平表面，冷藏至少4小时。脱模后装饰即可食用。'\n\n画面最底部是悬浮的白色应用交互底栏，左侧有一个浅灰色的椭圆形输入框，框内有灰色提示文字 '说点什么...'。底栏右侧依次排列着三个深灰色的线框图标：一个心形点赞图标，下方标注数字 '1.2w'；一个五角星收藏图标，下方标注数字 '8560'；以及一个带有三条横线的对话气泡评论图标。整体画面色彩以粉红、暖黄和纯白为主，光影通透，图文并茂地将复杂的制作过程具象化呈现。",
    "image": "https://eb118-file.cdn.bcebos.com/ernie-image/gallery_76_4.png",
    "revised_prompt_en": "A vertical screenshot of an image-and-text tutorial from a mobile social app, laid out in a top-to-bottom waterfall flow. The overall background is a warm, light beige, presenting a Japanese-style fresh food layout aesthetic. At the very top of the screen is the phone's system status bar, clearly displaying the time '14:30', a 5G signal icon, a Wi-Fi icon, and a full battery icon.\n\nBelow the status bar is a center-aligned, large-font main title in dark brown bold text: '法式草莓慕斯蛋糕 零失败教程' (French Strawberry Mousse Cake – Foolproof Tutorial). Beneath the title is a line of smaller, light pink English subtitle text: 'Strawberry Mousse Cake Recipe'.\n\nBelow the title, occupying roughly one-third of the frame, is a high-definition hero image of the finished product: a 6-inch pink mousse cake placed on a white marble round plate. The cake surface exhibits a smooth mirror glaze finish, with the top garnished by several halved bright red strawberries and scattered highlights of gold leaf. The background features a shallow depth-of-field blurred light-colored natural wood tabletop and a small sprig of eucalyptus. The lighting is soft, bright side natural light, accentuating the cake's dense, velvety texture and appealing color.\n\nBelow the hero image are four vertically arranged step-by-step sections. Each step section has a rounded-corner square process photo on the left and aligned black instructional text on the right.\n\nStep one: the left thumbnail shows a pair of hands pressing dark brown cookie crumbs firmly into a round push-bottom cake mold using the back of a metal spoon. The neatly typeset text on the right reads: '1. Cookie Base: Crush 80g digestive biscuits, mix with 40g melted unsalted butter, spread into the bottom of a 6-inch mold and press firmly, then refrigerate until needed.'\n\nStep two: the left thumbnail shows a small silver saucepan on a heat-conducting plate, with dark red strawberry pulp simmering and bubbling inside, faint white steam rising above. The text on the right reads: '2. Strawberry Filling: Dice 200g fresh strawberries, cook with 30g white granulated sugar and a small amount of lemon juice until thickened, add softened gelatin sheets (5g), pour into a small mold and freeze until set.'\n\nStep three: the left thumbnail shows a large transparent glass bowl containing a liquid with a soft, light pink hue being folded from bottom to top with a white silicone spatula. The text on the right reads: '3. Mousse Mixture: Blend 250g strawberries into a purée, gently heat to dissolve 10g gelatin sheets. After cooling to room temperature, gently fold together with 200g whipped cream (whipped to soft peaks / 60% whipped).'\n\nStep four: the left thumbnail shows the pink mousse mixture being poured from the rim of a bowl into the mold, with a faintly visible dark [layer in the center of the mold].",
