    "revised_prompt": "一张宽幅的彩色信息图，画面通过中央一条带有圆形节点装饰的白色垂直虚线，被平分为左右两个对比鲜明的部分。整体采用扁平化矢量插画与数据可视化结合的设计风格。\n\n画面左侧的主题为世界最高建筑，背景为深邃的藏青色向深紫色的夜空渐变，点缀着微亮的星星。顶部居中写着醒目的大写白色标题文字 'WORLD'S TOP 5 TALLEST BUILDINGS'。标题下方，从左至右排列着五座世界最高建筑的精细矢量插画，建筑物底部相连于一条象征地平线的白色基准线上，按高度从高到低排列。第一座是迪拜哈利法塔，呈现银灰色的阶梯状针型塔身，顶部带有发光天线，左侧引出一条白线连接着文字标签 '1. BURJ KHALIFA'、'Dubai' 和 '828m'。第二座是吉隆坡默迪卡118大厦，呈现多面体钻石切割反光玻璃立面，右侧标签为 '2. MERDEKA 118'、'Kuala Lumpur' 和 '678.9m'。第三座是上海中心大厦，呈现平滑螺旋上升的圆柱体结构，带有淡蓝绿色反光，标签为 '3. SHANGHAI TOWER'、'Shanghai' 和 '632m'。第四座是麦加皇家钟塔饭店，有着庞大的方形主楼、顶部的巨大金色发光钟面及标志性的新月顶饰，标签为 '4. ABRAJ AL-BAIT'、'Mecca' 和 '601m'。第五座是深圳平安金融中心，呈现笔直向上收束的现代不锈钢外墙质感大楼，标签为 '5. PING AN FINANCE CENTER'、'Shenzhen' 和 '599.1m'。所有建筑的窗户都亮着零星的黄色灯光，充满现代科技感。\n\n画面右侧的主题为甜品，背景为明亮的马卡龙粉色向嫩黄色的温暖渐变。顶部居中写着醒目的深粉色大写标题文字 'THE SWEETEST THINGS ON EARTH'。标题下方，采用网格交错排版展示了五种色彩鲜艳、具有光泽质感的甜品插画，每个甜品旁边都配有说明文字。左上角是一个覆盖着粉色糖霜并撒满彩色糖珠的甜甜圈，下方文字为 'GLAZED DONUT'、'Sugar content: 25g'、'A classic fried dough confection.'。右上角是一块切开的三层巧克力松露蛋糕，夹心流出浓郁的巧克力酱，旁边文字为 'CHOCOLATE CAKE'、'Rich cocoa layers'、'Dense, moist, and decadent.'。正中间是一个装着草莓、香草、芒果三球冰淇淋的华夫饼蛋筒，文字为 'RAINBOW GELATO'、'Fruit & Cream'、'Three scoops of melting sweet gelato.'。左下角是一罐透明玻璃瓶装的金黄色蜂蜜，带有一根沾满蜂蜜的木制滴管，文字为 'NATURAL HONEY'、'100% Pure'、'Produced by bees from flower nectar.'。右下角是一朵蓬松的蓝粉双色棉花糖，插在白色的纸棒上，文字为 'COTTON CANDY'、'Spun Sugar'、'Fluffy, cloud-like treat.'。右侧整体充满童话感与食物的圆润诱人质感，与左侧硬朗的建筑线条形成完美的视觉平衡与对比。",
    "image": "https://eb118-file.cdn.bcebos.com/ernie-image/gallery_89_2.png",
    "revised_prompt_en": "A wide-format color infographic, divided equally into two contrasting halves by a central white vertical dashed line decorated with circular nodes. The overall design style combines flat vector illustration with data visualization.\n\nThe left side of the image features the theme of the world's tallest buildings, with a background of deep navy blue transitioning to dark purple in a night sky gradient, dotted with faintly glowing stars. At the top center, prominent white uppercase title text reads 'WORLD'S TOP 5 TALLEST BUILDINGS'. Below the title, five detailed vector illustrations of the world's tallest buildings are arranged from left to right, with their bases connected to a white baseline symbolizing the horizon, ordered from tallest to shortest. The first is the Burj Khalifa in Dubai, depicted with a silver-gray stepped needle-shaped tower body with a glowing antenna at the top, with a white line extending from the left connecting to text labels reading '1. BURJ KHALIFA', 'Dubai', and '828m'. The second is the Merdeka 118 in Kuala Lumpur, featuring a polyhedral diamond-cut reflective glass façade, with labels on the right reading '2. MERDEKA 118', 'Kuala Lumpur', and '678.9m'. The third is the Shanghai Tower, depicted as a smooth spiraling cylindrical structure with a pale blue-green reflection, labeled '3. SHANGHAI TOWER', 'Shanghai', and '632m'. The fourth is the Abraj Al-Bait Clock Tower Hotel in Mecca, with a massive square main building, a large golden illuminated clock face at the top, and its iconic crescent finial, labeled '4. ABRAJ AL-BAIT', 'Mecca', and '601m'. The fifth is the Ping An Finance Center in Shenzhen, depicted as a straight, upward-tapering modern building with a stainless-steel exterior wall texture, labeled '5. PING AN FINANCE CENTER', 'Shenzhen', and '599.1m'. All buildings have scattered yellow window lights glowing, conveying a sense of modern technology.\n\nThe right side of the image features the theme of desserts, with a background of bright macaron pink transitioning to a warm soft yellow gradient. At the top center, prominent dark pink uppercase title text reads 'THE SWEETEST THINGS ON EARTH'. Below the title, five vibrantly colored dessert illustrations with glossy textures are displayed in a staggered grid layout, each dessert",
