    "revised_prompt": "一幅1920年代Arthur Rackham风格的复古童话插画。采用横向构图，展现了一片幽暗深邃的魔法森林。整体色调为低饱和度的柔和水彩，以赭石、橄榄绿、复古棕和褪色的靛蓝为主，背景带有陈旧羊皮纸的肌理质感。画风使用极其细腻复杂的黑色墨水线条勾勒轮廓与交叉阴影，充满神秘、迷人且略带诡异的氛围。画面两侧和背景生长着巨大的古树，树干表皮粗糙，纹理中隐约透出扭曲的人脸轮廓。树根像枯瘦的爪子一样牢牢抓住布满青苔的岩石和泥土。扭曲、纠缠的树枝在头顶交织成穹顶，遮蔽了天空，只漏下几缕昏暗的苍白光线，照亮了地面的藤蔓和巨大的蕨类植物。画面中央的空地上，一只穿着维多利亚时代破旧天鹅绒马甲、胸前挂着怀表链的野兔正靠在一簇巨大的红盖白点蘑菇上。左侧树枝上，停着一只目光锐利的老乌鸦，脖子上挂着一串生锈的小铃铛。树根的缝隙间和半空中，飞舞着几只长着蜻蜓翅膀、面容略显苍白诡异的半透明小妖精，它们手里提着散发微光的微型提灯。右侧的低矮灌木中，一只戴着单片眼镜的巨大蟾蜍蹲在覆盖着地衣的石头上。场景中隐藏着多种魔法物品：中央蘑菇的根部泥土里露出一把发光的紫色水晶钥匙；左侧老树的一个树洞里放着一个流淌着银色细沙的古董沙漏；蟾蜍身边的水洼底部沉着一个散发着金色微光、指针疯狂旋转的罗盘。画面顶部中央悬浮着优雅、飘逸的黑色手写书法风格标题：'The Whispering Woods'。在画面右下角的羊皮纸留白区域，用古典斜体手写字写着一段谜语：'I have no voice, but I sing in the wind. I have no eyes, but I watch from the shadows. Seek the key beneath the red cap to find the truth.'",
    "image": "https://eb118-file.cdn.bcebos.com/ernie-image/gallery_20_2.png",
    "revised_prompt_en": "A vintage fairy-tale illustration in the style of 1920s Arthur Rackham. In a horizontal composition, it presents a dark, profound enchanted forest. The overall palette consists of desaturated, soft watercolors dominated by ochre, olive green, antique brown, and faded indigo, with the background carrying the textural quality of aged parchment. The artistic style employs extraordinarily delicate and intricate black ink lines for contours and cross-hatching, imbuing the scene with a mysterious, enchanting, and slightly eerie atmosphere. On both sides and in the background grow enormous ancient trees with rough, gnarled bark, their textures faintly revealing twisted humanoid face contours. The roots grip moss-covered rocks and soil like gaunt claws. Twisted, entangled branches interweave overhead into a canopy that blocks the sky, allowing only a few dim, pale shafts of light to filter through and illuminate the ground-level vines and giant ferns. In a clearing at the center, a hare wearing a tattered Victorian-era velvet waistcoat with a pocket watch chain across its chest leans against a cluster of large red-capped, white-spotted mushrooms. On a branch to the left perches a sharp-eyed old crow with a string of small rusted bells around its neck. In the crevices among tree roots and in midair, several semi-transparent small faeries with dragonfly wings and slightly pale, uncanny faces flutter about, carrying faintly glowing miniature lanterns. In the low shrubbery on the right, an enormous toad wearing a monocle squats on a lichen-covered stone. Multiple magical objects are hidden throughout the scene: at the base of the central mushrooms, a glowing purple crystal key protrudes from the soil; inside a hollow of the old tree on the left sits an antique hourglass with silver sand streaming through it; at the bottom of a puddle near the toad lies a compass emitting a golden glow with its needle spinning wildly. At the top center of the image floats an elegant, flowing black hand-lettered calligraphic title: 'The Whispering Woods'. In a blank parchment area at the lower right corner, a riddle is written in classical italic handwriting: 'I have no voice, but I sing in the wind. I have no eyes, but I watch from the shadows. Seek the key beneath the red cap to find the truth.'",
    "prompt_zh": "将这张图片转化为1920年代风格的童话插画，采用Arthur Rackham的画风。使用柔和的水彩色调和精细的墨线勾勒。在场景中填充奇幻的森林生物、扭曲的树枝和隐藏的魔法物品。整体基调应神秘、迷人，略带诡异感。添加手写书法风格的标题和谜语。"
