    "prompt": "<instruction>\n \nInput A is a Specific Dish \nInput B is a City or Landscape \nMap the food ingredients to Geographical Features: If input A is not given, choose food ingredients that are popular for this city or landscape\nThe Liquid (The Water): Identify the sauce, broth, or syrup.\n(e.g., Pizza Sauce -> Canals. Ramen Broth -> Harbor. Syrup -> River).\nThe Solid (The Land): Identify the primary carb or protein.\n(e.g., Melted Cheese -> Pavement/Sand. Noodles -> Winding Roads. Pancake Stack -> Mountain Plateau).\nThe Garnish (The Vegetation): Identify herbs or veggies.\n(e.g., Basil/Broccoli -> Trees. Green Onions -> Grass).\n  Container (The Serving Vessel):\nGoal: \"Edible Diorama\" Macro Photography.\nThe Boundary: The crust, bowl rim, or plate edge acts as the physical horizon or city wall preventing the \"world\" from spilling out.\nThe Setting: A rustic wooden dining table visible in the blurred periphery.\nThe Architecture :\n Construction: Miniature input b buildings rise directly from the \"Solid\" layer (Cheese/Noodles).\nMateriality: The input B buildings mimic the texture of the food.\n(e.g., Venetian houses made of crust/dough with pepperoni roofs. Tokyo skyscrapers made of stacked tofu or french fries).\nIntegration: The structures look baked or cooked into the scene, not just placed on top.\n Narrative Scale :\nScale: 1:87 scale (HO Scale) miniature figures.\nTransit: Vehicles or boats interact with the \"Liquid\" layer.\n(e.g., Tiny Gondolas floating in the red Tomato Sauce canal. Ships floating in the Ramen broth).\nThe Life: Tiny people are dining at tables on the cheese or walking along the crust-shoreline.\nLighting & Atmosphere:\nLighting: Warm Food Styling Light. Highlights the glisten of the sauce/oil and the texture of the crust.\nFocus: Tilt-Shift. The center of the \"City\" is sharp; the edges of the pizza/bowl blur out to sell the miniature scale.\nOutput: ONE image, 1:1 Aspect Ratio, Macro Photography, \"Foodscape\" aesthetic, Appetizing and Surreal.\n</instruction>",
    "prompt_en": "<instruction>\n \nInput A is a Specific Dish \nInput B is a City or Landscape \nMap the food ingredients to Geographical Features: If input A is not given, choose food ingredients that are popular for this city or landscape\nThe Liquid (The Water): Identify the sauce, broth, or syrup.\n(e.g., Pizza Sauce -> Canals. Ramen Broth -> Harbor. Syrup -> River).\nThe Solid (The Land): Identify the primary carb or protein.\n(e.g., Melted Cheese -> Pavement/Sand. Noodles -> Winding Roads. Pancake Stack -> Mountain Plateau).\nThe Garnish (The Vegetation): Identify herbs or veggies.\n(e.g., Basil/Broccoli -> Trees. Green Onions -> Grass).\n  Container (The Serving Vessel):\nGoal: \"Edible Diorama\" Macro Photography.\nThe Boundary: The crust, bowl rim, or plate edge acts as the physical horizon or city wall preventing the \"world\" from spilling out.\nThe Setting: A rustic wooden dining table visible in the blurred periphery.\nThe Architecture :\n Construction: Miniature input b buildings rise directly from the \"Solid\" layer (Cheese/Noodles).\nMateriality: The input B buildings mimic the texture of the food.\n(e.g., Venetian houses made of crust/dough with pepperoni roofs. Tokyo skyscrapers made of stacked tofu or french fries).\nIntegration: The structures look baked or cooked into the scene, not just placed on top.\n Narrative Scale :\nScale: 1:87 scale (HO Scale) miniature figures.\nTransit: Vehicles or boats interact with the \"Liquid\" layer.\n(e.g., Tiny Gondolas floating in the red Tomato Sauce canal. Ships floating in the Ramen broth).\nThe Life: Tiny people are dining at tables on the cheese or walking along the crust-shoreline.\nLighting & Atmosphere:\nLighting: Warm Food Styling Light. Highlights the glisten of the sauce/oil and the texture of the crust.\nFocus: Tilt-Shift. The center of the \"City\" is sharp; the edges of the pizza/bowl blur out to sell the miniature scale.\nOutput: ONE image, 1:1 Aspect Ratio, Macro Photography, \"Foodscape\" aesthetic, Appetizing and Surreal.\n</instruction>",
