    "title_en": "Steampunk Neural Network Cross-Section",
    "prompt": "Generate a diagram of a two-layer neural network in the style of Stephen Biesty",
    "prompt_en": "Generate a diagram of a two-layer neural network in the style of Stephen Biesty",
    "source": "https://twitter.com/jon_barron/status/1991554563233779822",
    "type": "t2i",
    "author": "@jon_barron",
    "author_link": "https://twitter.com/jon_barron/status/1991554563233779822",
    "revised_prompt": "一幅斯蒂芬·比斯蒂（Stephen Biesty）风格的手绘横截面剖视图插画，背景为略微泛黄的复古羊皮纸纹理。画面以极高密度的水彩和墨水线条，将一个两层神经网络具象化为一座巨大、复杂且充满蒸汽朋克和复古工业感的机械工厂。构图呈横向展开，信息流从左向右传递。\n\n画面正上方有一幅展开的羊皮卷轴横幅，上面用复古衬线字体写着 'TWO-LAYER NEURAL NETWORK: A CROSS-SECTIONAL VIEW'。\n\n画面左侧为输入区，顶部挂着木制标牌 'INPUT LAYER' 和 'Data Entry Port'。该区域由三个巨大的砖砌与黄铜相间的漏斗状建筑组成，漏斗外壁分别涂有清晰的标识 'x1'、'x2' 和 'x3'。建筑被纵向剖开，露出内部的齿轮传送带。许多微小且极其精细的工人（身穿复古蓝色工装和安全帽）正推着装满数据块的矿车，将原材料倾倒入漏斗中。\n\n连接左侧漏斗与中部区域的是错综复杂的管道和电缆桥架，顶部有指示牌 'WEIGHTS PIPELINE' 和 'Synaptic Connections'。这些管道粗细不一，代表不同的权重值。管道网络之间搭建着多层木制脚手架和螺旋楼梯。数十名微小的工人正在架子上忙碌，有的正用巨大的扳手奋力转动管道上的黄铜阀门，旁边带有黑色墨水注释 'Worker calibrating the weight valve'。\n\n画面中央为隐藏层，顶部悬挂巨大铸铁标牌 'HIDDEN LAYER'。该区域包含四座巨大的圆柱形机械处理塔，标注为 'Neuron Processing Unit'。这四座塔均呈剖面展示，内部包含复杂的活塞、旋转的离心机以及底部燃烧着橙色火焰的巨大锅炉，锅炉外壳标注着 'Activation Boiler'。每座处理塔旁边都连接着一个悬空的小型水箱，有液体不断注入主塔，水箱上挂着写有 'Bias Generator' 的标签。工人们在塔内的铁丝网栈道上巡逻，查看压力表盘。\n\n画面右侧为输出层，标牌上写着 'OUTPUT LAYER' 和 'Prediction Generator'。这里是两座精密的分类冲压机，接收来自中央塔的细长管道。机器顶部装备着巨大的机械指针表盘、复杂的发条装置和闪烁的灯泡。最终产品经过冲压和分类后，由两条传送带送出，分别装入两个巨大的木板箱中，箱体外侧用醒目的红色油漆刷有 'y1' 和 'y2'。整个画面充满了极端的机械细节，如无数的铆钉、砖缝、泄压阀喷出的蒸汽、纵横交错的走道，完美呈现了比斯蒂那种令人惊叹的工业剖切图美学。",
    "image": "https://eb118-file.cdn.bcebos.com/ernie-image/gallery_55_2_v2.png",
    "revised_prompt_en": "A hand-drawn cross-sectional cutaway illustration in the style of Stephen Biesty, set against a slightly yellowed vintage parchment texture background. The scene uses extremely high-density watercolor and ink linework to visualize a two-layer neural network as a massive, complex mechanical factory imbued with steampunk and retro-industrial aesthetics. The composition extends horizontally, with information flowing from left to right.\n\nAt the very top of the image, an unfurled parchment scroll banner bears the text 'TWO-LAYER NEURAL NETWORK: A CROSS-SECTIONAL VIEW' in a vintage serif typeface.\n\nOn the left side of the image is the input area, with a wooden sign hanging at the top reading 'INPUT LAYER' and 'Data Entry Port.' This area consists of three enormous funnel-shaped structures built from alternating brick and brass, with the outer walls of each funnel clearly labeled 'x1,' 'x2,' and 'x3.' The buildings are cut away longitudinally, revealing internal gear-driven conveyor belts. Numerous tiny, exquisitely detailed workers (wearing vintage blue overalls and hard hats) are pushing ore carts filled with data blocks, tipping raw materials into the funnels.\n\nConnecting the left-side funnels to the central area is an intricate network of pipes and cable trays, with signs at the top reading 'WEIGHTS PIPELINE' and 'Synaptic Connections.' These pipes vary in thickness, representing different weight values. Multi-level wooden scaffolding and spiral staircases are erected between the pipe networks. Dozens of tiny workers are bustling about on the scaffolding; some are straining to turn brass valves on the pipes with enormous wrenches, accompanied by a black ink annotation reading 'Worker calibrating the weight valve.'\n\nAt the center of the image is the hidden layer, with a massive cast-iron sign suspended from above reading 'HIDDEN LAYER.' This area contains four enormous cylindrical mechanical processing towers, labeled 'Neuron Processing Unit.' All four towers are shown in cross-section, revealing complex pistons, spinning centrifuges, and massive boilers at their bases burning with orange flames, with the boiler casings labeled 'Activation Boiler.' Each processing tower is connected to a small, suspended water tank from which liquid continuously flows into the main tower, with a sign hanging on the tank reading 'Bias Gen",
    "prompt_zh": "以Stephen Biesty的风格生成一幅双层神经网络示意图。"
