    "revised_prompt": "一张带有2006年早期数码相机质感的略微模糊的竖幅风景照片。画面中下方，一位徒步者背对镜头，停留在一条崎岖的土路上，眺望着远方。徒步者背着一个巨大的深蓝色登山背包，背包外部绑着灰色的防潮垫，侧面插着水壶。徒步者穿着红色的冲锋衣、卡其色速干长裤和厚实的棕色登山靴。土路从画面正下方蜿蜒向中景延伸，路面上散落着碎石，两侧生长着低矮的高山草甸灌木丛和几棵常绿的松树。远景是壮观的落基山脉（Rockies），连绵起伏的灰色岩石山峰高耸入云，山顶和山谷间点缀着零星的白色积雪，层峦叠嶂的轮廓占据了画面的上半部分。天空布满了厚重的灰白色云层，漫反射的柔和光线笼罩着整个场景，营造出一种广袤而宁静的自然氛围。画面呈现出早期数码相机的典型特征：整体焦点略微模糊，边缘不够锐利，暗部带有轻微的数字噪点，色彩略显黯淡且具有年代感。画面右下角有清晰可见的橙黄色早期数码相机时间戳文字：'08/15/2006'。利用竖向构图完美展现了土路的纵深感与山脉的高大巍峨。",
    "image": "https://eb118-file.cdn.bcebos.com/ernie-image/item_1544_1.png",
    "revised_prompt_en": "A slightly blurry vertical landscape photograph with the quality of an early 2006 digital camera. In the lower-center of the frame, a hiker stands with their back to the camera on a rugged dirt trail, gazing into the distance. The hiker carries a large dark blue mountaineering backpack with a gray sleeping pad strapped to the outside and a water bottle tucked into the side pocket. The hiker wears a red hardshell jacket, khaki quick-dry pants, and sturdy brown hiking boots. The dirt trail winds from the very bottom of the frame toward the middle ground, its surface scattered with loose gravel, flanked by low alpine meadow shrubs and a few evergreen pines. The background features the spectacular Rocky Mountains—towering, undulating gray rock peaks rising into the clouds, with patches of white snow dotting the summits and valleys, their layered ridgeline silhouettes occupying the upper half of the frame. The sky is blanketed with heavy gray-white clouds, and diffused soft light envelops the entire scene, creating a vast and tranquil natural atmosphere. The image exhibits the typical characteristics of an early digital camera: the overall focus is slightly soft, edges lack sharpness, shadows carry mild digital noise, and the colors appear somewhat muted with a dated quality. In the lower-right corner, there is a clearly visible orange-yellow early digital camera timestamp text: '08/15/2006'. The vertical composition perfectly showcases the depth of the trail and the towering grandeur of the mountain range.",
