    "filename": "item_1767_4.png",
    "index": 1767,
    "title": "儿童科学插画：细胞分裂",
    "title_en": "Kids Science Illustration: Cell Division",
    "prompt": "Make me a detailed diagram showing how mitosis works,, with annotations and visual explanations, organized at a primary school level.",
    "prompt_en": "Make me a detailed diagram showing how mitosis works,, with annotations and visual explanations, organized at a primary school level.",
    "source": "https://twitter.com/emmanuel_2m/status/1991591659478364574",
    "type": "t2i",
    "author": "@ShreyaYadav___",
    "author_link": "https://twitter.com/emmanuel_2m/status/1991591659478364574",
    "revised_prompt": "一张面向小学生的科学教育插画图解，采用横向宽幅构图，背景为柔和的浅黄色，色彩鲜明、画风可爱且充满童趣。画面四周散落着手绘风格的彩色星星和螺旋线装饰。画面顶部中央是醒目的大号彩色卡通风格标题文字 'How Cells Divide: The Magic of Mitosis!'。标题下方有一段黑色的副标题说明文字：'Mitosis is how one cell becomes two identical cells. This helps us grow and heal!'。画面主体从左到右依次排列了五个代表细胞分裂阶段的插图，每个阶段之间用粗壮的橙色手绘箭头连接。\n\n第一个插图（最左侧）：一个浅蓝色的圆形细胞，长着一对可爱的豆豆眼和一个笑脸。细胞中心有一个深蓝色的细胞核，里面画着乱糟糟的细线代表DNA。插图上方的标签文字为 '1. Getting Ready (Interphase)'，下方的说明文字为 'The cell grows and copies its DNA (instructions).'。\n\n第二个插图：细胞核的边缘变成了虚线，表示正在溶解。原本乱糟糟的线变成了四个颜色鲜艳（红色和绿色）的“X”形染色体。上方的标签文字为 '2. Packing Up (Prophase)'，下方的说明文字为 'The DNA packs tightly into X-shapes called chromosomes.'。\n\n第三个插图：四个“X”形染色体整齐地排列在细胞正中央的垂直线上。细胞左右两端各有一个橙色的中心体，伸出黄色的虚线（纺锤丝）像绳子一样连接到每个染色体的中心。上方的标签文字为 '3. Lining Up (Metaphase)'，下方的说明文字为 'The chromosomes line up right in the middle of the cell.'。\n\n第四个插图：细胞整体被拉长成了椭圆形。“X”形染色体被从中间劈开，变成了“V”形，正被黄色的虚线拉向细胞的左右两端。上方的标签文字为 '4. Moving Apart (Anaphase)'，下方的说明文字为 'Special ropes pull the chromosome halves to opposite sides.'。\n\n第五个插图（最右侧）：细胞上下中间部分向内凹陷，像一个葫芦。两端分别形成了新的细胞核，里面的DNA重新变回了线团状。箭头进一步指向两个较小、完全独立且长着开心笑脸的浅蓝色圆形细胞（代表子细胞）。上方的标签文字为 '5. Splitting (Telophase & Cytokinesis)'，下方的说明文字为 'The cell pinches in the middle and makes two perfect copies!'。",
    "image": "https://eb118-file.cdn.bcebos.com/ernie-image/item_1767_4.png",
    "revised_prompt_en": "A science education illustration designed for elementary school students, using a horizontal wide-format composition with a soft light yellow background, vibrant colors, and a cute, childlike art style. Scattered around the edges of the image are hand-drawn style colorful stars and spiral line decorations. At the top center of the image is a prominent large colorful cartoon-style title text reading 'How Cells Divide: The Magic of Mitosis!'. Below the title is a line of black subtitle explanatory text: 'Mitosis is how one cell becomes two identical cells. This helps us grow and heal!'. The main body of the image features five illustrations representing the stages of cell division arranged from left to right, with each stage connected by thick orange hand-drawn arrows.\n\nThe first illustration (far left): A light blue circular cell with a pair of cute beady eyes and a smiley face. At the center of the cell is a dark blue nucleus with tangled thin lines drawn inside representing DNA. The label text above the illustration reads '1. Getting Ready (Interphase)', and the explanatory text below reads 'The cell grows and copies its DNA (instructions).'.\n\nThe second illustration: The edge of the nucleus has become a dashed line, indicating it is dissolving. The previously tangled lines have transformed into four brightly colored (red and green) \"X\"-shaped chromosomes. The label text above reads '2. Packing Up (Prophase)', and the explanatory text below reads 'The DNA packs tightly into X-shapes called chromosomes.'.\n\nThe third illustration: Four \"X\"-shaped chromosomes are neatly aligned along a vertical line at the very center of the cell. On each end (left and right) of the cell is an orange centrosome, extending yellow dashed lines (spindle fibers) that connect like ropes to the center of each chromosome. The label text above reads '3. Lining Up (Metaphase)', and the explanatory text below reads 'The chromosomes line up right in the middle of the",
    "prompt_zh": "为我制作一张展示有丝分裂工作原理的详细图解，带有标注和视觉说明，以小学生能理解的水平进行组织编排。"
}, {
    "filename": "item_1774_1.png",
