    "title": "CAR-T细胞疗法流程图",
    "title_en": "CAR-T Cell Therapy Flowchart",
    "prompt": "In an illustration describe all of the stages of CAR-T cell therapy from lab to patients.",
    "prompt_en": "In an illustration describe all of the stages of CAR-T cell therapy from lab to patients.",
    "source": "https://twitter.com/DeryaTR_/status/1991558446429409554",
    "type": "t2i",
    "author": "@HBCoop_",
    "author_link": "https://twitter.com/DeryaTR_/status/1991558446429409554",
    "revised_prompt": "一张横版科学信息图表插画，展示了CAR-T细胞疗法从实验室到患者的完整阶段流程。画面背景为干净的医疗风格，采用深蓝色到浅蓝色的渐变，带有微弱的网格线和细胞结构的背景底纹。整体构图采用顺时针的环状流程布局，各个阶段通过带有箭头的发光虚线相互连接。画面正上方居中印有醒目的白色加粗主标题文字：'CAR-T Cell Therapy Process'。\n\n画面按流程包含以下六个具体的阶段图文细节：\n\n左上角为第一阶段，包含白色数字和标题：'1. Leukapheresis'。下方配有说明文字：'Blood is drawn from the patient to extract T cells.' 图像主体为一个抽象的人体轮廓躺在病床上，手臂连接着医疗管线，血液顺着管子流入一台小型的血细胞分离机中，机器旁画有几个蓝色的圆形小球体代表提取出的T细胞。\n\n右上角为第二阶段，包含数字和标题：'2. Reprogramming'。下方配有说明文字：'T cells are genetically modified in the lab to produce Chimeric Antigen Receptors (CARs) on their surface.' 图像主体为一个实验室培养皿和一支移液管，旁边是一个放大的微观特写：一个代表慢病毒载体的六边形结构正在将一段发光的基因链注入蓝色的T细胞中，该T细胞表面开始长出数个亮绿色的'Y'字型受体（CAR）。\n\n右侧中部为第三阶段，包含数字和标题：'3. Expansion'。下方配有说明文字：'Millions of CAR-T cells are grown in a laboratory bioreactor.' 图像主体为一个透明的圆柱形生物反应器容器，内部漂浮着密密麻麻、数量众多的带有亮绿色'Y'型受体的蓝色CAR-T细胞，表示细胞的大量增殖。\n\n右下角为第四阶段，包含数字和标题：'4. Patient Preparation'。下方配有说明文字：'The patient undergoes brief chemotherapy to prepare the body.' 图像主体为一个带红十字的日历图标和一个带有透明液体的静脉滴注袋，象征患者在接受清淋化疗。\n\n左下角为第五阶段，包含数字和标题：'5. Infusion'。下方配有说明文字：'The modified CAR-T cells are infused back into the patient.' 图像主体为一个装满蓝色CAR-T细胞的静脉输液袋，通过一条发光的管线重新连接回第一阶段中那个人体轮廓的另一只手臂上。\n\n左侧中部为第六阶段，包含数字和标题：'6. Attacking Cancer'。下方配有说明文字：'CAR-T cells bind to cancer cells and destroy them.' 图像主体为一个放大的微观场景：数个带'Y'型亮绿色受体的蓝色CAR-T细胞，精准地将其受体嵌合在一个巨大的、表面长满突起的紫色癌细胞的抗原上。紫色癌细胞的边缘呈现出破裂、溶解的碎片特效，表示癌细胞正在被消灭。\n\n整幅插画风格专业、清晰，色彩对比鲜明，蓝色和亮绿色用于强调T细胞及其人工受体，紫色用于代表病变细胞，确保医学科普信息的传达准确且视觉丰富。",
    "image": "https://eb118-file.cdn.bcebos.com/ernie-image/item_1782_4.png",
    "revised_prompt_en": "A horizontal scientific infographic illustration showcasing the complete staged process of CAR-T cell therapy from laboratory to patient. The background features a clean medical style with a dark blue to light blue gradient, accompanied by faint grid lines and cell structure watermark patterns. The overall composition adopts a clockwise circular flow layout, with each stage interconnected by glowing dashed lines with arrows. Centered at the top of the image is a prominent white bold main title: 'CAR-T Cell Therapy Process'.\n\nThe image contains the following six specific staged visual and textual details arranged by process flow:\n\nThe upper left corner is the first stage, with white numerals and title: '1. Leukapheresis'. Below is the explanatory text: 'Blood is drawn from the patient to extract T cells.' The main visual depicts an abstract human silhouette lying on a hospital bed, with the arm connected to medical tubing, blood flowing through the tube into a small apheresis machine, beside which several small blue spheres represent the extracted T cells.\n\nThe upper right corner is the second stage, with numerals and title: '2. Reprogramming'. Below is the explanatory text: 'T cells are genetically modified in the lab to produce Chimeric Antigen Receptors (CARs) on their surface.' The main visual shows a laboratory culture dish and a pipette, alongside a magnified microscopic close-up: a hexagonal structure representing a lentiviral vector is injecting a glowing gene strand into a blue T cell, on whose surface several bright green 'Y'-shaped receptors (CARs) are beginning to grow.\n\nThe right-center area is the third stage, with numerals and title: '3. Expansion'. Below is the explanatory text: 'Millions of CAR-T cells are grown in a laboratory bioreactor.' The main visual depicts a transparent cylindrical bioreactor vessel, inside which densely packed, numerous blue CAR-T cells bearing bright green 'Y'-shaped receptors are floating, representing the cells'",
    "prompt_zh": "用一幅插图描述 CAR-T 细胞疗法从实验室到患者的所有阶段。"
