    "filename": "item_1814_2.png",
    "index": 1814,
    "title": "神经网络工厂剖面插画",
    "title_en": "Neural Network Factory Cross-Section Illustration",
    "prompt": "Generate a diagram of a two-layer neural network in the style of Stephen Biesty",
    "prompt_en": "Generate a diagram of a two-layer neural network in the style of Stephen Biesty",
    "source": "https://twitter.com/jon_barron/status/1991554563233779822",
    "type": "t2i",
    "author": "@_philschmid",
    "author_link": "https://twitter.com/jon_barron/status/1991554563233779822",
    "revised_prompt": "一张斯蒂芬·比斯蒂（Stephen Biesty）风格的复杂截面剖视插画，呈现竖版构图。画面主体是一座被垂直剖开的、宏伟的维多利亚时期多层机械工厂，整体被巧妙地设计成一个两层神经网络的结构。插画采用极其精细的墨水线稿和柔和复古的水彩晕染，充满密集的微观细节。工厂最顶层代表输入层，设有三个巨大的黄铜漏斗状接收室，数百个微小的、穿着复古工作服的工人正忙碌地将象征数据的方块推入漏斗中，旁边带有细线引出的标签，上面写着 'Input Layer'、'x1'、'x2' 和 'x3'。顶层下方是错综复杂的管道、滑轮和交织的传送带网络，将物质向下输送；管道上装有巨大的金属阀门，小工人们正悬挂在上面转动阀门轮盘以调节流量，代表着权重，旁边有标签写着 'Weights'。工厂的中层是庞大的隐藏层，并排安置着四个巨大的球形蒸汽锅炉（象征神经元节点），锅炉的金属外壳被部分剖开，露出内部正在运转的复杂齿轮和沸腾的流体。工程师们拿着剪贴板在锅炉间的金属走道上巡视，查看布满指针的仪表盘，引出的标签上写着 'Hidden Layer'、'Activation'、'Node 1'、'Node 2'、'Node 3' 和 'Node 4'。从这些锅炉底部延伸出的管道再次交织汇聚，通向工厂的最底层——输出层。底层设有两台精密的终端冲压机，正在将汇聚的流体转化为最终的实体模块，并输出到检验台上，一位戴着高礼帽的工厂主正在仔细查看机器吐出的长条纸带，旁边的标签写着 'Output Layer'、'Prediction'、'y1' 和 'y2'。建筑的剖切面清晰地展示了红砖墙体、厚重的木桁架和铆接的钢梁。画面色调以羊皮纸的暖黄色、生锈的铁红色、复古黄铜色以及柔和的水蓝色为主，整体风格既具有极强的工业机械感，又富有幽默生动的微观叙事性。",
    "image": "https://eb118-file.cdn.bcebos.com/ernie-image/item_1814_2.png",
    "revised_prompt_en": "A complex cutaway cross-section illustration in the style of Stephen Biesty, presented in a vertical/portrait composition. The main subject is a magnificent Victorian-era multi-story mechanical factory, sliced open vertically, ingeniously designed to represent the structure of a two-layer neural network. The illustration employs extremely fine ink line work with soft, vintage watercolor washes, brimming with dense microscopic details. The topmost floor of the factory represents the input layer, featuring three enormous brass funnel-shaped receiving chambers where hundreds of tiny workers in vintage overalls busily push data-symbolizing blocks into the funnels, with fine-line leader labels reading 'Input Layer,' 'x1,' 'x2,' and 'x3.' Below the top floor is an intricate network of pipes, pulleys, and interwoven conveyor belts transporting material downward; the pipes are fitted with massive metal valves, with small workers hanging from them turning valve wheels to regulate flow, representing weights, with labels reading 'Weights.' The middle level of the factory is the expansive hidden layer, housing four enormous spherical steam boilers (symbolizing neuron nodes) arranged side by side, their metal casings partially cut away to reveal complex gears in operation and boiling fluids inside. Engineers carrying clipboards patrol the metal walkways between the boilers, inspecting gauge panels bristling with needles, with leader labels reading 'Hidden Layer,' 'Activation,' 'Node 1,' 'Node 2,' 'Node 3,' and 'Node 4.' Pipes extending from the bottoms of these boilers interweave and converge once more, leading to the factory's lowest level—the output layer. The bottom floor houses two precision terminal stamping machines, converting the converged fluids into final solid modules and outputting them onto inspection tables, where a factory owner wearing a top hat carefully examines long paper tape strips extruded by the machines, with labels reading 'Output Layer,' 'Prediction,' 'y1,' and 'y2.' The cut-away face of the building clearly reveals red brick walls, heavy timber trusses, and riveted steel beams. The color palette is dominated by warm parchment yellow, rusty iron red, vintage brass tones, and soft aqua blue. The overall style combines a strong industrial-mechanical aesthetic with humorous and vivid microscopic narrative charm.",
    "prompt_zh": "以Stephen Biesty的风格生成一个两层神经网络的示意图。"
