    "revised_prompt": "一张手绘风格的等距视角建筑示意图，横向构图，背景带有复古米黄色工程纸的质感。画面中心细致地绘制了著名的地标建筑——伦敦塔桥。建筑主体采用严谨的等距透视（isometric）画法，线条为深灰色手绘墨水质感，保留了部分建筑草图的透视辅助线和用于表现光影的交叉排线。塔桥的两座哥特式主塔矗立在画面中央，结构层次分明，细致描绘了砖石缝隙、拱门窗户和顶部的尖塔。两塔之间上层的水平人行通道清晰可见，而下方的开启桥面被刻画为向上呈45度角张开的状态，展示其内部结构。桥塔两侧延伸出悬索结构，连接着两端的引桥。桥下的泰晤士河以简约的手绘平行波浪线示意。\n\n画面中包含丰富的图纸标注和引线说明文字。左上角用复古的建筑手写体写有醒目的大标题 'TOWER BRIDGE'，其下方是稍小的副标题 'LONDON, UK - COMPLETED 1894'。围绕建筑主体，有细直线引出并指向特定结构，配有如下文字标注：指向高层人行道的引线旁写着 'HIGH-LEVEL WALKWAY'；分别指向两座塔楼的文字为 'NORTH TOWER' 和 'SOUTH TOWER'；指向侧边悬挂链条的文字为 'SUSPENSION CHAIN'；指向张开的中心桥面的文字为 'BASCULE (OPENING SPAN)'；指向水面桥墩基座的文字为 'PIER & ENGINE ROOM'；下方的水面波浪线旁标注着 'RIVER THAMES'。\n\n在画面的左侧空白处，绘制了一个简约的齿轮与传动轴的局部放大透视图，用于展示桥面的内部驱动系统，其上方标注有 'HYDRAULIC MECHANISM'。画面右下角绘制了一个带有手绘质感的指北针图标（顶部标注字母 'N'）以及一条线段比例尺，上方写着 'SCALE 1:1000'。整幅画面呈现出兼具工程严谨性与手绘艺术感的复古图纸风格。",
    "image": "https://eb118-file.cdn.bcebos.com/ernie-image/item_2145_1.png",
    "revised_prompt_en": "A hand-drawn style isometric architectural illustration in landscape orientation, with a background featuring the texture of vintage beige engineering paper. At the center of the image, the famous landmark—Tower Bridge of London—is meticulously rendered. The main structure is drawn in rigorous isometric perspective, with lines in a deep gray hand-drawn ink texture, retaining some of the architectural sketch's perspective guide lines and cross-hatching used to convey light and shadow. The two Gothic main towers of Tower Bridge stand prominently at the center of the image, with clearly defined structural layers, finely depicting the masonry joints, arched windows, and pinnacles at the top. The upper-level horizontal pedestrian walkway between the two towers is clearly visible, while the lower bascule bridge deck is depicted in a state of opening at a 45-degree angle, revealing its internal structure. Suspension chain structures extend from both sides of the bridge towers, connecting to the approach spans on either end. The River Thames beneath the bridge is indicated with simple hand-drawn parallel wavy lines.\n\nThe image contains abundant drawing annotations and leader line descriptions. In the upper left corner, a prominent main title 'TOWER BRIDGE' is written in vintage architectural hand-lettering, with a slightly smaller subtitle beneath it reading 'LONDON, UK - COMPLETED 1894'. Around the main structure, fine straight leader lines extend outward pointing to specific structural elements, accompanied by the following text annotations: beside the leader line pointing to the high-level walkway is written 'HIGH-LEVEL WALKWAY'; the text pointing to the two towers respectively reads 'NORTH TOWER' and 'SOUTH TOWER'; the text pointing to the side suspension chains reads 'SUSPENSION CHAIN'; the text pointing to the opening center bridge deck reads 'BASCULE (OPENING SPAN)'; the text pointing to the pier base at the water surface reads 'PIER & ENGINE ROOM'; and beside the wavy lines representing the water below is annotated 'RIVER THAMES'.\n\nIn the blank space on the left side of the image, a simplified close-up perspective drawing of gears and a drive shaft is rendered, used to illustrate the internal drive system of the bridge deck, with 'HYDRAULIC MECHANISM' annotated above it. In the lower right corner, a hand-drawn style compass rose icon (with the letter 'N' annotated at the top) and a linear scale bar are drawn, with 'SCALE 1:1000' written above. The entire image presents a vintage technical drawing style that combines engineering rigor with hand-drawn artistic sensibility.",
    "prompt_zh": "创建一幅 [LANDMARK] 的手绘等距示意图。尺寸为 1080x1080。"
