    "author_link": "https://x.com/AllaAisling/status/2009284710862643206",
    "revised_prompt": "横向排版的汽车品牌历史学家的档案记录板插图，全面展示了1962款法拉利250 GTO Berlinetta的详尽信息。画面整体从左至右呈现出视觉风格的平滑渐变：从左侧做旧的米白色档案纸张质感，过渡到中部的精确工程图纸风格，最终在右侧变为高饱和度的复古汽车动态摄影。画面分为左、中、右三个主要区域，底部贯穿一条宽大的黑色标题栏。\n\n左侧区域展示出厂档案文档，背景为带有时间痕迹的米色复古纸张。上方是一张边缘泛黄的原始规格表，带有清晰的打字机字体英文：'SPECIFICATIONS: FERRARI 250 GTO 1962'，下方分行列出 'Engine: 3.0 L Colombo V12' 以及 'Power: 300 hp at 7500 rpm'。规格表下方并排固定着两张黑白色的生产线老照片，清晰展示了穿着工装的工人正在手工敲打组装铝制车身框架。照片下方有一张复古报纸的广告剪报，印有法拉利跃马标志和粗体意大利文 'La Nuova Berlinetta'。该区域最下方是一张手写的底盘编号注册卡片，用黑色墨水笔迹写有 'Chassis: 3757GT' 和 'Date: June 1962'。\n\n中间区域为精细的技术图解，背景带有蓝灰色工程图纸的网格线质感。核心主体是一辆红色法拉利250 GTO的透视图（Phantom view），车身外壳呈现半透明状，清晰显露出内部复杂的动力总成，包括前置V12发动机、六个并排的Weber化油器以及连接后桥的传动轴。透视图周围布满细致的白色指示线与工程标注文字：引向发动机的文字为 '3.0L TIPO 168 COMP. V12'，引向底盘前部的文字为 'UNEQUAL LENGTH WISHBONES'，车尾处绘有表现气流方向的白色虚线并标注 'Kamm Tail Aerodynamics'，车身侧面引出文字 'Scaglietti Aluminum Body'。透视图下方印有复古排版的赛车成绩单，文字为 '1962 24 Hours of Le Mans: 3rd Overall, 2nd in Class'。\n\n右侧区域占据画面的三分之一，是一幅充满动感的复古汽车摄影照片。一辆涂装为鲜艳法拉利红（Rosso Corsa）的250 GTO正在勒芒赛道的弯道中疾驰，车门上带有白底黑字的赛事编号。画面采用摇摄手法表现出强烈的速度感，赛车主体对焦清晰，而背景的赛道边缘、看台和蓝天白云呈现出强烈的横向运动模糊（motion blur）。摄影风格呈现出1960年代柯达胶片的高饱和度与复古色调特征。\n\n画面最下方的黑色横向标题栏内，用白色的现代无衬线粗体大写字母印制了极具视觉冲击力的信息：'FERRARI 250 GTO — CHASSIS NO. 3757GT, 3RD OVERALL 1962 LE MANS 24 HOURS, SCUDERIA FERRARI'。",
    "image": "https://eb118-file.cdn.bcebos.com/ernie-image/item_2201_3.png",
    "revised_prompt_en": "A landscape-oriented automobile brand historian's archival record board illustration, comprehensively presenting detailed information on the 1962 Ferrari 250 GTO Berlinetta. The overall image exhibits a smooth visual style gradient from left to right: transitioning from the distressed cream-white archival paper texture on the left, through the precise engineering drawing style in the center, and finally into high-saturation vintage automotive action photography on the right. The image is divided into three main zones—left, center, and right—with a broad black title bar running across the bottom.\n\nThe left zone displays factory archival documents, with a background of vintage beige paper bearing the marks of time. At the top is an original specification sheet with yellowed edges, featuring clear typewriter-font English text: 'SPECIFICATIONS: FERRARI 250 GTO 1962', with lines listed below reading 'Engine: 3.0 L Colombo V12' and 'Power: 300 hp at 7500 rpm'. Below the specification sheet, two black-and-white production line archival photographs are affixed side by side, clearly showing workers in coveralls hand-hammering and assembling the aluminum body frame. Beneath the photographs is a vintage newspaper advertising clipping, printed with the Ferrari prancing horse logo and bold Italian text 'La Nuova Berlinetta'. At the very bottom of this zone is a handwritten chassis number registration card, with black ink handwriting reading 'Chassis: 3757GT' and 'Date: June 1962'.\n\nThe center zone features detailed technical illustrations, with a background bearing the grid-line texture of blue-gray engineering paper. The core subject is a phantom view of a red Ferrari 250 GTO, with the body shell rendered semi-transparent, clearly revealing the complex internal powertrain, including the front-mounted V12 engine, six side-by-side Weber carburetors, and the drive shaft connecting to the rear axle. The phantom view is surrounded by meticulous white leader lines and engineering annotation text: the text leading to the engine reads '3.0L TIPO 168 COMP. V12', the text leading to the front chassis reads 'UNEQUAL LENGTH WISHBONES', at the rear of the car white dashed lines indicating airflow direction are drawn and annotated 'Kamm Tail Aerodynamics', and from the side of the body a leader line extends with the text 'Scaglietti A",
    "prompt_zh": "一块品牌历史学家的 [VEHICLE] — [MODEL / VARIANT / YEAR] 文献展示板。左侧部分：工厂文献资料，包括原始规格表、生产线照片、时期广告以及底盘编号登记册。中间部分：技术插图，以透视剖面图展示动力总成、悬挂几何结构、空气动力学标注及材料说明，周围环绕着同时期的赛事成绩或车辆传承记录。右侧部分：车辆处于其标志性环境中，无论是赛道、山口还是林荫大道，均以符合该时期的色彩调色风格拍摄。"
