    "revised_prompt_en": "In a minimalist-composition vertical high-fashion photography frame, the center showcases an elegant haute couture gown made entirely of transparent bubble wrap. The dress is completely hollow inside, with no objects or model supporting it, presenting a three-dimensional suspended state as if worn by an invisible person. This bubble wrap dress features exquisite tailoring, including a fitted waist design and a naturally draping, voluminous skirt hem. The material is crystal-clear and highly glossy, with extremely rich detail, hyper-realistically reproducing the physical texture of inflated plastic bubbles—each neatly arranged, plump bubble refracts delicate highlights and clear contours under the light. The frame employs soft, diffused studio lighting that evenly penetrates and illuminates the transparent dress body, eliminating harsh shadows and enhancing the material's translucency. The background is a pure, neutral light-gray seamless backdrop with no extraneous objects or decorations, creating an exceptionally clean, modern, and minimalist visual aesthetic. The overall presentation achieves a high-fashion editorial style with photorealistic rendering, with an extremely sharp focal point that perfectly highlights the unique texture born from the collision between the everyday bubble wrap material and the elegant fashion silhouette.",
