    "revised_prompt_en": "An ultra-sharp minimalist editorial infographic, shot from a 90-degree top-down flat-lay perspective. Landscape orientation, on a light grayish-white clean background at the very center of the frame, a pure white ceramic coffee cup is placed, containing a high-quality caramel macchiato with an elaborate latte art pattern and a crosshatch caramel drizzle on the surface, exhibiting natural food coloring. Surrounding the coffee cup is a fund flow infographic. It adopts a monochromatic UI style (black, white, gray) paired with vivid emerald green as the sole accent color, presenting a premium visual quality reminiscent of Apple UI combined with *National Geographic*, with clearly structured typographic hierarchy. In the upper-left corner, there is a prominent, extra-bold sans-serif high-contrast large headline: 'THE REAL COST OF YOUR COFFEE,' immediately followed below by the large total price figure: '$5.00,' serving as the visual focal point. From the central coffee cup, thin dark-gray arrows radiate outward in all directions, connecting to various cost breakdowns. The arrow to the upper right points to an emerald-green donut chart, accompanied by prominent text reading 'PROFIT,' '10%,' and '$0.50.' The arrow to the middle right connects to a dark-gray horizontal progress bar representing labor costs, with text reading 'LABOR,' '30%,' and '$1.50.' The arrow to the lower right connects to a progress bar and a small building icon representing rent, with text reading 'RENT,' '25%,' and '$1.25.' The arrow to the middle left connects to a coffee bean icon and progress bar, with text reading 'INGREDIENTS,' '15%,' and '$0.75.' The arrow to the lower left connects to a gear icon and progress bar, with text reading 'OPERATIONS,' '10%,' and '$0.50.' Two arrows at the bottom point to packaging and branding respectively, each accompanied by a paper cup icon and a megaphone icon, with text reading 'PACKAGING,' '5%,' '$0.25,' and 'BRANDING,' '5%,' '$0.25.'